sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User
    participant Main as main (app/qt or app/wt)
    participant App as ClientApplication
    participant Core as CoreModule
    participant Login as LoginDialog
    participant Backend
    participant Profile
    participant Modules as Domain modules
    participant MW as MainWindowModule

    User->>Main: launch client.exe
    Main->>Main: parse command line, install translator
    Main->>App: new ClientApplication(ctx)
    activate App
    App->>Core: new CoreModule(executor)
    Core-->>App: tracer, command registries, progress host
    Note right of App: also: transport_factory_, master_data_services_
    deactivate App

    Main->>App: Start()
    activate App
    App->>Login: login_handler_(ctx)
    activate Login
    Login->>User: prompt credentials and backend
    User-->>Login: username, password, backend
    Login->>Backend: connect and authenticate
    Backend-->>Login: services
    Login-->>App: DataServices
    deactivate Login

    App->>App: PostLogin()
    App->>Profile: Load()
    Profile-->>App: window layouts, pages, prefs

    rect rgb(245, 245, 250)
    Note over App,Modules: Construct domain modules in dependency order
    App->>Modules: EventModule, TimedDataService, TaskManager, ConnectionStateReporter, WriteService
    App->>Modules: ConfigurationModule, DebuggerModule, FileSystemComponent
    App->>Modules: FavoritesModule, PortfolioModule
    App->>Modules: ModusModule, VidiconModule (Qt only)
    App->>Modules: ExportConfigurationModule
    end

    App->>MW: new MainWindowModule(ctx)
    activate MW
    MW->>Profile: read pages and window definitions
    MW->>MW: instantiate views via ControllerRegistry
    MW->>User: display main window
    deactivate MW
    deactivate App

    Note over User,MW: After bootstrap the UI is live - events stream in via EventFetcher and values via the monitored-item subscription

